1
00:01:35,601 --> 00:01:36,600
Will you marry me?

2
00:01:36,601 --> 00:01:38,058
Kabir... please.

3
00:01:38,434 --> 00:01:39,392
Okay.

4
00:01:40,393 --> 00:01:42,058
Will you marry me, please?

5
00:01:43,434 --> 00:01:44,392
Why are you doing this?

6
00:01:45,309 --> 00:01:47,183
Because sooner or later we will.

7
00:01:48,518 --> 00:01:49,725
We love each other.

8
00:01:50,393 --> 00:01:52,725
Our families seem to
tolerate each other.

9
00:01:53,809 --> 00:01:56,767
I'm an architect and you're
an interior designer.

10
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:58,560
We're perfect.

11
00:02:01,978 --> 00:02:03,060
What do you say?

12
00:02:04,478 --> 00:02:05,519
Are you sure?

13
00:02:06,436 --> 00:02:08,519
Natasha, please make it quick...

14
00:02:08,603 --> 00:02:09,269
my knee is hurting.

15
00:02:11,395 --> 00:02:12,352
Yes!

16
00:02:30,311 --> 00:02:34,852
It seems like only yesterday that
Natasha came into this world.

17
00:02:35,395 --> 00:02:36,560
And today she's getting engaged.

18
00:02:38,270 --> 00:02:40,311
Kabir, I'm not losing a daughter.

19
00:02:41,396 --> 00:02:42,811
I'm gaining a son.

20
00:02:43,522 --> 00:02:44,562
You're so filmy, dad.

21
00:02:48,397 --> 00:02:49,396
Excuse me!

22
00:02:49,397 --> 00:02:50,104
Harryji

23
00:02:52,313 --> 00:02:55,437
Two years ago you commissioned
me to build your hotel.

24
00:02:56,438 --> 00:02:59,312
Who would've imagined that
one day we'll be a big family.

25
00:02:59,688 --> 00:03:02,729
On behaIf of my family,
I welcome you all.

26
00:03:03,313 --> 00:03:04,146
Thank you so much.

27
00:03:04,688 --> 00:03:08,187
Did you ever know that you're my hero

28
00:03:09,438 --> 00:03:12,521
You're everything I wish I could be

29
00:03:13,855 --> 00:03:17,104
I can fly like an eagle

30
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:22,522
Cause you're the wind beneath my wings

31
00:03:23,898 --> 00:03:29,731
You're the wind beneath my wings

32
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:35,564
- That was lovely.

33
00:03:36,565 --> 00:03:37,564
Wonderful.

34
00:03:41,232 --> 00:03:42,064
Hello everyone.

35
00:03:42,065 --> 00:03:43,273
I am Imran.

36
00:03:43,982 --> 00:03:45,398
Kabir and I have been
friends since school.

37
00:03:45,649 --> 00:03:46,939
The three Musketeers!

38
00:03:47,274 --> 00:03:50,148
That's right, it was the name
uncle had given the three of us.

39
00:03:50,482 --> 00:03:51,439
The three Musketeers.

40
00:03:52,232 --> 00:03:54,523
Unfortunately, the third musketeer...

41
00:03:54,524 --> 00:03:56,523
Arjun is not with us anymore.

42
00:03:58,399 --> 00:04:01,398
Don't worry, he's alive. He
just isn't here right now.

43
00:04:03,399 --> 00:04:04,399
Anyway, Natasha...

44
00:04:04,775 --> 00:04:07,524
Kabir is one of the nicest guys ever.

45
00:04:08,483 --> 00:04:11,065
So, if you ever smash
his BMW, don't worry.

46
00:04:12,441 --> 00:04:13,483
Good excuse to get a new car.
- Absolutely.

47
00:04:14,776 --> 00:04:17,358
He's also very intelligent.

48
00:04:18,692 --> 00:04:20,733
So leave the kid's homework to him.

49
00:04:21,317 --> 00:04:22,483
You're a true friend, thanks.

50
00:04:22,484 --> 00:04:23,441
You're welcome, bro.

51
00:04:24,401 --> 00:04:26,483
He's very large hearted.

52
00:04:27,026 --> 00:04:28,858
So, don't think twice...

53
00:04:28,859 --> 00:04:30,233
just buy those diamonds.

54
00:04:30,234 --> 00:04:31,358
Okay.

55
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:38,233
Basically Natasha...

56
00:04:38,776 --> 00:04:40,775
Kabir is a solid guy.

57
00:04:41,817 --> 00:04:44,316
Put your hand in his and walk with him.

58
00:04:45,609 --> 00:04:46,942
Because no matter what...

59
00:04:47,277 --> 00:04:48,442
he will never let you down.

60
00:04:49,402 --> 00:04:50,776
- So sweet.
- Hear, hear!

61
00:04:53,443 --> 00:04:54,401
Thank you.

62
00:04:54,485 --> 00:04:55,609
You can send the cheque now.

63
00:04:57,485 --> 00:04:58,360
Tanya...

64
00:04:59,528 --> 00:05:00,360
thank you.

65
00:05:01,319 --> 00:05:02,568
Let me warn you...

66
00:05:02,778 --> 00:05:05,277
Nikhil is planning a full
power bachelor party.

67
00:05:05,569 --> 00:05:06,402
Too late.

68
00:05:06,403 --> 00:05:09,277
His school friends have
planned a bachelor holiday.

69
00:05:09,403 --> 00:05:10,402
A road trip...

70
00:05:10,694 --> 00:05:11,443
through Spain.

71
00:05:12,028 --> 00:05:13,860
- A road trip?
- Don't ask.

72
00:05:14,403 --> 00:05:16,777
They had made some
pact in college that...

73
00:05:16,778 --> 00:05:19,860
each one would choose
an adventure sport...

74
00:05:19,861 --> 00:05:21,902
Are you serious?
Like Fear Factor?

75
00:05:22,528 --> 00:05:23,527
Exactly!

76
00:05:23,611 --> 00:05:25,985
And the other two would have to do it.

77
00:05:26,653 --> 00:05:27,902
So, what have you picked?

78
00:05:28,403 --> 00:05:29,861
That I can't say.

79
00:05:31,070 --> 00:05:32,569
Not in front of me, at least.

80
00:05:33,695 --> 00:05:34,569
You see...

81
00:05:34,654 --> 00:05:37,944
the sport we pick is a
surprise for the other two.

82
00:05:38,529 --> 00:05:39,528
Shut up!

83
00:05:39,570 --> 00:05:41,028
- Seriously.
- Are you kidding me?

84
00:05:41,487 --> 00:05:42,487
No.

85
00:05:42,613 --> 00:05:45,487
That ensures none of us back out.

86
00:05:46,488 --> 00:05:48,070
Whose idea was this?

87
00:05:48,488 --> 00:05:49,279
Mine.

88
00:05:49,988 --> 00:05:50,612
Three weeks.

89
00:05:50,863 --> 00:05:52,279
You know how these boys are.

90
00:05:52,696 --> 00:05:53,320
Not Kabir.

91
00:05:54,113 --> 00:05:55,320
Oh please!

92
00:05:55,488 --> 00:05:58,195
All guys go crazy at bachelor parties.

93
00:05:59,321 --> 00:06:00,404
In fact...

94
00:06:00,405 --> 00:06:05,320
Nikhil still hasn't told me
what happened at his.

95
00:06:06,613 --> 00:06:07,445
I don't know.

96
00:06:08,488 --> 00:06:10,945
I heard something
about your bachelor party.

97
00:06:16,489 --> 00:06:17,530
Who told you?

98
00:06:17,656 --> 00:06:18,613
So it is true.

99
00:06:19,614 --> 00:06:20,488
Does Natasha know?

100
00:06:21,489 --> 00:06:22,696
No man, why would I tell her?

101
00:06:23,114 --> 00:06:24,446
Please... don't tell her.

102
00:06:26,406 --> 00:06:27,364
She was from Ukraine.

103
00:06:28,698 --> 00:06:30,114
- Bloody hot!
- Nice.

104
00:06:30,615 --> 00:06:31,447
I was sloshed.

105
00:06:32,907 --> 00:06:33,947
Okay, listen...

106
00:06:34,407 --> 00:06:36,781
If Sameera finds out about
this, she'll kill me.

107
00:06:37,490 --> 00:06:38,739
I know, don't worry.

108
00:06:38,823 --> 00:06:42,031
It was my last night as a bachelor.
You know I'd never do it otherwise.

109
00:06:42,032 --> 00:06:44,072
I understand, don't worry about it.

110
00:06:44,073 --> 00:06:45,072
- Please.
- It happens.

111
00:06:46,573 --> 00:06:47,531
Sameera!

112
00:06:51,198 --> 00:06:52,239
Sorry, I couldn't resist.

113
00:06:53,073 --> 00:06:54,907
- Take care, man.
- See you.

114
00:06:57,866 --> 00:07:00,615
Trust me, this trick never fails.

115
00:07:01,199 --> 00:07:02,698
What do you mean?

116
00:07:02,699 --> 00:07:07,365
Well, you tell people you
know something about them...

117
00:07:07,449 --> 00:07:10,448
and before you know it,
they tell you their secrets.

118
00:07:10,449 --> 00:07:11,865
Shut up!

119
00:07:11,866 --> 00:07:14,116
You didn't know about the Ukrainian?

120
00:07:14,617 --> 00:07:15,824
No, he just told me.

121
00:07:17,242 --> 00:07:18,824
Mind blowing!

122
00:07:21,242 --> 00:07:24,033
- Yeah, well time equals money, Simon.
You want money, stop wasting my time.

123
00:07:24,700 --> 00:07:26,574
Sell 50,000 June contracts!

124
00:07:26,659 --> 00:07:28,949
50,000 and don't screw up
my stop losses this time!

125
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:30,991
How much?

126
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,408
Damn! That's horrendous!

127
00:07:34,242 --> 00:07:35,616
Sell it. Sell everything.

128
00:07:43,201 --> 00:07:45,450
Listen Joe, if you continue to
give me bullshit fills like that...

129
00:07:45,451 --> 00:07:47,617
I'm going to have to trade my
Ferrari in for a Ford Fiesta!

130
00:07:48,118 --> 00:07:49,450
He doesn't like pink.

131
00:07:50,410 --> 00:07:52,617
We have white and gold and...

132
00:07:53,243 --> 00:07:54,534
tonnes of champagne.

133
00:07:54,910 --> 00:07:55,700
And...

134
00:07:56,826 --> 00:07:58,076
- the centre piece.
- This is Nice.

135
00:07:59,077 --> 00:07:59,951
Finally!

136
00:08:00,411 --> 00:08:01,243
Kabira!

137
00:08:01,619 --> 00:08:03,285
Sorry man.

138
00:08:03,411 --> 00:08:05,076
You have no idea what's happening here.

139
00:08:05,286 --> 00:08:07,493
And you have no idea what
a nice party you missed.

140
00:08:08,411 --> 00:08:09,451
I'm sure, man.

141
00:08:10,036 --> 00:08:11,076
Listen...

142
00:08:11,411 --> 00:08:12,701
I've a problem.

143
00:08:13,619 --> 00:08:15,035
I can't make it to Spain.

144
00:08:15,036 --> 00:08:15,451
- What?!

145
00:08:16,786 --> 00:08:18,410
Arjun, you promised!

146
00:08:18,411 --> 00:08:20,119
I know but...

147
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:23,161
I thought this deal I'm working
on would come through...

148
00:08:23,328 --> 00:08:23,911
- but I'm stuck.

149
00:08:24,412 --> 00:08:27,411
I can't believe you're ditching
me on my bachelor trip.

150
00:08:28,412 --> 00:08:29,536
It's not that...

151
00:08:29,537 --> 00:08:30,994
- Then what is it?

152
00:08:31,328 --> 00:08:33,661
We had decided to do this together.

153
00:08:35,412 --> 00:08:37,869
If you can't make it,
I'm calling it off.

154
00:08:38,287 --> 00:08:40,577
Don't get sentimental.
It's my work!

155
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:42,287
I'm not.

156
00:08:42,288 --> 00:08:45,120
It's been cancelled once
before, so let's do it again.

157
00:08:45,121 --> 00:08:46,495
It's fine.

158
00:08:47,704 --> 00:08:51,287
It's either the three of
us going or none at all.

159
00:09:15,414 --> 00:09:16,496
Hey...

160
00:09:17,455 --> 00:09:18,121
Hi.

161
00:09:18,414 --> 00:09:18,996
How are you?

162
00:09:19,622 --> 00:09:20,454
Good.

163
00:09:21,705 --> 00:09:23,663
Looking good, you've been working out?

164
00:09:24,330 --> 00:09:24,788
Yes.

165
00:09:25,455 --> 00:09:26,829
I usually come in the morning.

166
00:09:32,206 --> 00:09:33,997
I was going to call you.

167
00:09:34,873 --> 00:09:35,872
Then why didn't you?

168
00:09:37,623 --> 00:09:38,789
I'm getting married.

169
00:09:43,081 --> 00:09:45,456
- That was quick.
- Arjun, please!

170
00:09:50,624 --> 00:09:51,790
All the best, Rohini.

171
00:10:09,499 --> 00:10:11,415
- Arjun, it's me again.

172
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:13,707
- Don't ditch me.

173
00:10:13,708 --> 00:10:16,291
- I know why you're making excuses.

174
00:10:16,875 --> 00:10:18,874
- But it's been four
years for that incident.

175
00:10:18,875 --> 00:10:19,832
- I'm getting married now.

176
00:10:20,875 --> 00:10:23,124
- Even today, I only have two friends.

177
00:10:24,083 --> 00:10:27,458
- We're the three Musketeers.
All for one, one for all.

178
00:10:33,459 --> 00:10:35,167
Have you thought about...

179
00:10:36,459 --> 00:10:37,500
what we spoke?

180
00:10:38,251 --> 00:10:38,792
About what?

181
00:10:40,543 --> 00:10:43,458
Are you moving back to Bombay?

182
00:10:44,251 --> 00:10:45,208
Ammi...

183
00:10:46,043 --> 00:10:49,000
I like Delhi and living on my own.

184
00:10:55,626 --> 00:10:58,501
And this trip to Spain...

185
00:10:58,502 --> 00:11:01,334
is it a coincidence or did you plan it?

186
00:11:03,627 --> 00:11:05,876
Why don't you just say
what you're really thinking?

187
00:11:07,502 --> 00:11:08,459
Fine.

188
00:11:09,419 --> 00:11:11,210
Do you intend to meet Salman?

189
00:11:12,545 --> 00:11:13,919
I don't know.

190
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:15,960
Imran, why don't you trust me?

191
00:11:16,545 --> 00:11:18,502
It's not about you Ammi.

192
00:11:18,503 --> 00:11:20,710
- He is my father.
- He's your father?

193
00:11:20,711 --> 00:11:25,919
Has he ever called you or
tried to find out how you are?

194
00:11:26,003 --> 00:11:28,002
Maybe he did and you kept it from me.

195
00:11:29,628 --> 00:11:31,835
Until recently I wasn't even
aware that he is my father.

196
00:11:33,295 --> 00:11:34,335
Alright.

197
00:11:34,628 --> 00:11:36,002
Do what you want.

198
00:11:36,003 --> 00:11:38,419
But please remember this.

199
00:11:38,420 --> 00:11:40,460
Faisal was your only father.

200
00:11:46,504 --> 00:11:48,670
- Hello there.
- Hello.

201
00:11:49,212 --> 00:11:50,628
I can see you.

202
00:11:50,629 --> 00:11:52,629
I miss you, baby.

203
00:11:52,630 --> 00:11:55,212
Now we can see each other everyday.

204
00:11:55,547 --> 00:11:57,879
I'm only going for three weeks, Natasha.

205
00:12:06,588 --> 00:12:08,962
What will I do in London all alone?

206
00:12:09,505 --> 00:12:11,504
You'll shop.

207
00:12:11,505 --> 00:12:15,754
And in three weeks I'll come to
London to carry your shopping bags.

208
00:12:15,838 --> 00:12:17,837
- Very funny.
- I know.

209
00:15:55,848 --> 00:15:57,389
Thank you.

210
00:15:58,640 --> 00:16:00,722
So how many miles are we driving?
- We're on road for three weeks.

211
00:16:00,807 --> 00:16:02,889
- I don't see Madrid in this plan.
- Because it's not there.

212
00:16:02,890 --> 00:16:04,722
- We travel to Spain but we're
not going to see the capital?

213
00:16:04,807 --> 00:16:06,889
- We don't have enough time.

214
00:16:06,890 --> 00:16:08,515
- We can't change it now.
- I think we should.

215
00:16:08,599 --> 00:16:10,015
Look who's here!

216
00:16:11,434 --> 00:16:13,641
- Welcome! How was your flight?
- Hello.

217
00:16:14,434 --> 00:16:15,724
Well...

218
00:16:15,725 --> 00:16:16,974
it flew.

219
00:16:17,517 --> 00:16:18,474
Funny!

220
00:16:27,225 --> 00:16:29,683
- Good to see you.
- You too.

221
00:16:29,684 --> 00:16:30,766
I'm sorry about Abu.

222
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:33,391
I got your email.

223
00:16:34,517 --> 00:16:36,141
- How's Ammi?
- She's fine.

224
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,891
It's not easy to get over these things.

225
00:16:40,434 --> 00:16:41,433
How've you been?

226
00:16:41,642 --> 00:16:42,516
I'm good.

227
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:44,016
Pretty good actually.

228
00:16:44,017 --> 00:16:46,183
I've a new apartment.
Three bedrooms, big space.

229
00:16:46,850 --> 00:16:47,849
Nice.

230
00:16:47,850 --> 00:16:50,225
I can't believe we're together again.

231
00:16:50,226 --> 00:16:51,850
- Yeah.
- Finally!

232
00:16:52,351 --> 00:16:53,184
Should we sit?

233
00:16:54,268 --> 00:16:56,060
So, here is the plan.

234
00:16:56,436 --> 00:16:57,685
First...

235
00:16:57,686 --> 00:17:00,393
we go to Costa Brava,
which is my choice.

236
00:17:01,227 --> 00:17:02,893
Then Arjun wants to go to Seville.

237
00:17:03,436 --> 00:17:04,935
And then we'll head to... Sevia.

238
00:17:04,936 --> 00:17:06,435
Pampalona which you've chosen.

239
00:17:06,436 --> 00:17:08,685
Tomorrow morning we
leave for Costa Brava.

240
00:17:15,352 --> 00:17:16,643
What are you doing with the laptop?

241
00:17:17,061 --> 00:17:18,518
I'm looking for an address.

242
00:17:18,519 --> 00:17:19,643
Hola Kabira.

243
00:17:23,102 --> 00:17:24,476
Kabira...
- Yes.

244
00:17:25,019 --> 00:17:26,060
Your treasure.

245
00:17:27,352 --> 00:17:28,935
Brilliant. Thanks a ton.

246
00:17:33,228 --> 00:17:34,811
What have you done to this?

247
00:17:35,312 --> 00:17:36,394
Dude!

248
00:17:36,478 --> 00:17:40,061
First of all, be thankful that I
bought this 12,000 Euro bag for you!

249
00:17:40,062 --> 00:17:40,937
What?

250
00:17:42,521 --> 00:17:43,103
Here... show, show...

251
00:17:47,604 --> 00:17:49,645
12,000 Euro for this purse?
- Yes.

252
00:17:50,021 --> 00:17:51,437
Way more than your salary.

253
00:17:54,688 --> 00:17:55,395
What?

254
00:17:56,604 --> 00:17:57,978
Natasha loves these bags.

255
00:17:58,563 --> 00:17:59,562
And I love cars, Kabir.

256
00:18:00,563 --> 00:18:01,520
Always remember.

257
00:18:01,646 --> 00:18:03,687
If you ever want to gift
me an expensive car...

258
00:18:03,813 --> 00:18:05,645
don't hesitate.

259
00:18:05,646 --> 00:18:06,937
I won't.

260
00:18:06,938 --> 00:18:07,437
Good.

261
00:18:07,438 --> 00:18:08,437
Let's go.

262
00:18:08,438 --> 00:18:09,853
I can't.

263
00:18:10,521 --> 00:18:12,562
I need to make some calls.

264
00:18:12,563 --> 00:18:13,312
I'll see you guys later.

265
00:18:14,605 --> 00:18:16,063
Adios amigos.

266
00:18:17,272 --> 00:18:19,521
- I thought this was a holiday.
- Me too.

267
00:18:20,147 --> 00:18:21,729
Let's go.

268
00:18:22,064 --> 00:18:23,021
We take the next right.

269
00:18:27,231 --> 00:18:28,564
- Looks quite old.
- There it is.

270
00:18:32,523 --> 00:18:33,689
There is the cathedral.

271
00:18:35,148 --> 00:18:37,189
- Do you know where this place is?
- Yes, straight ahead.

272
00:18:37,481 --> 00:18:39,064
How far is this gallery?

273
00:18:39,898 --> 00:18:40,855
