- Their mobiles are switched off.

1614
01:55:47,832 --> 01:55:48,789
- What?
- Yup.

1615
01:55:48,915 --> 01:55:50,039
Even Nuria's?

1616
01:55:50,040 --> 01:55:51,456
Yes, I'm shocked.

1617
01:55:51,582 --> 01:55:54,664
When she knew we'd land up in jail, she
should've kept the phone switched on

1618
01:55:56,123 --> 01:55:58,122
If our bail isn't posted...

1619
01:55:58,123 --> 01:56:00,539
we'll be stuck here for days.

1620
01:56:05,083 --> 01:56:05,915
Arjun...

1621
01:56:07,749 --> 01:56:09,498
tell them I want to make a call.

1622
01:56:10,541 --> 01:56:11,707
To whom?

1623
01:56:12,791 --> 01:56:14,082
Salman Habib.

1624
01:56:14,458 --> 01:56:15,498
The artist?

1625
01:56:17,333 --> 01:56:17,915
Yeah.

1626
01:56:19,416 --> 01:56:21,123
Why will he come to post our bail?

1627
01:56:23,124 --> 01:56:24,040
Are you alright?

1628
01:56:24,916 --> 01:56:27,416
Just because we can't reach
anyone, he's losing it.

1629
01:56:27,417 --> 01:56:28,499
He's my father.

1630
01:56:29,334 --> 01:56:29,958
What?

1631
01:56:32,542 --> 01:56:33,708
I am his son.

1632
01:56:44,126 --> 01:56:45,125
Just let it go Imran.

1633
01:56:47,960 --> 01:56:49,042
Just let it go.

1634
01:56:49,501 --> 01:56:50,084
- Hello...

1635
01:56:51,585 --> 01:56:53,042
Hello, may l...

1636
01:56:53,043 --> 01:56:54,959
speak with Mr. Salman Habib, please?

1637
01:56:55,918 --> 01:56:56,584
- Yes?

1638
01:56:58,126 --> 01:57:00,042
Sir, I am Imran.

1639
01:57:01,960 --> 01:57:04,334
I am Rahila's son.

1640
01:57:08,710 --> 01:57:10,043
When did you find out?

1641
01:57:13,419 --> 01:57:15,293
A few days after Abu died.

1642
01:57:18,044 --> 01:57:21,626
In his stuff, I found a letter
that Ammi had written to him.

1643
01:57:22,919 --> 01:57:24,835
The letter stated that...

1644
01:57:24,961 --> 01:57:30,586
Ammi was grateful that Abu had
accepted her and her unborn child.

1645
01:57:34,003 --> 01:57:35,461
Why didn't you tell us?

1646
01:57:38,503 --> 01:57:39,919
I was a bit shaken up.

1647
01:57:41,587 --> 01:57:44,002
What would I tell you?
Abu is not my father.

1648
01:57:46,795 --> 01:57:48,752
He loved you a lot.

1649
01:57:50,170 --> 01:57:51,961
He really loved you.

1650
01:57:53,878 --> 01:57:55,045
And us.

1651
01:57:55,921 --> 01:57:57,962
I mean, think about it.

1652
01:57:57,963 --> 01:58:00,378
Be it sports day or
parent-teacher meetings...

1653
01:58:00,379 --> 01:58:03,795
our fathers seldom came,
but Abu was always there.

1654
01:58:05,338 --> 01:58:07,587
Well, my father was dead.

1655
01:58:07,963 --> 01:58:11,379
So, if he showed up for sports day
it would've been a bit strange.

1656
01:58:18,297 --> 01:58:19,796
- You've got bail.

1657
01:58:23,130 --> 01:58:24,254
They're here.

1658
01:58:35,922 --> 01:58:37,004
Hi.

1659
01:58:40,048 --> 01:58:40,797
Imran.

1660
01:58:43,048 --> 01:58:44,005
Imran...

1661
01:58:45,090 --> 01:58:46,005
I'm Salman.

1662
01:58:50,756 --> 01:58:52,840
My friends, Arjun and Kabir.

1663
01:58:52,841 --> 01:58:53,923
- Hello.
- Thank you.

1664
01:58:53,924 --> 01:58:55,298
Hi... thank you.

1665
01:58:56,216 --> 01:58:58,215
You three look pretty hungover.

1666
01:59:01,591 --> 01:59:04,340
You're welcome to come over
to my place and freshen up.

1667
01:59:04,966 --> 01:59:07,840
Our bags and car are at the hotel.

1668
01:59:08,132 --> 01:59:09,381
I'll drive you there.

1669
01:59:11,174 --> 01:59:12,048
Come.

1670
01:59:27,008 --> 01:59:29,049
- Wow, this is beautiful.

1671
01:59:30,717 --> 01:59:31,757
It's really nice.

1672
01:59:33,008 --> 01:59:35,008
Are you always so polite?

1673
01:59:36,634 --> 01:59:39,967
It's absolute rubbish.
Anyone can do that.

1674
01:59:40,759 --> 01:59:43,133
This gentleman, my neighbour...

1675
01:59:43,134 --> 01:59:46,383
was obsessed with having his
wife immortalised in a portrait.

1676
01:59:46,384 --> 01:59:50,050
So, I applied my brush
and fuIfilled his desire.

1677
01:59:50,134 --> 01:59:52,300
And with his money, paid my bills.

1678
01:59:54,759 --> 01:59:56,925
So, what are you guys doing in Seville?

1679
01:59:57,801 --> 01:59:59,008
Skydiving.

1680
01:59:59,009 --> 02:00:00,217
- Really?
- Yeah.

1681
02:00:00,301 --> 02:00:02,467
So, you jumped out of a
plane and landed in jail?

1682
02:00:03,801 --> 02:00:05,008
You could say that.

1683
02:00:05,593 --> 02:00:09,759
That apart, what do you do?

1684
02:00:10,760 --> 02:00:12,259
Well, I'm a financial broker.

1685
02:00:12,760 --> 02:00:13,718
In London.

1686
02:00:14,094 --> 02:00:15,134
Money man.

1687
02:00:16,720 --> 02:00:17,385
And you?

1688
02:00:17,928 --> 02:00:19,802
My family is in the
construction business.

1689
02:00:20,845 --> 02:00:23,052
Well, never mind.
Everyone makes mistakes.

1690
02:00:24,011 --> 02:00:25,010
That's funny.

1691
02:00:25,553 --> 02:00:27,552
You're a Xerox copy of him.

1692
02:00:31,178 --> 02:00:33,052
And, what about you?

1693
02:00:34,303 --> 02:00:35,177
I write.

1694
02:00:37,011 --> 02:00:37,469
What?

1695
02:00:38,303 --> 02:00:39,969
I'm a copywriter in advertising.

1696
02:00:41,053 --> 02:00:44,135
Writing copy for ads is like
a buffet for the masses.

1697
02:00:44,636 --> 02:00:47,219
For instance, this painting
is for someone else.

1698
02:00:48,803 --> 02:00:51,552
Do you write anything
to feed your own soul?

1699
02:00:53,178 --> 02:00:54,595
I do.

1700
02:00:59,347 --> 02:00:59,971
Sir?

1701
02:01:00,180 --> 02:01:00,971
Salman.

1702
02:01:01,847 --> 02:01:03,512
Right. We'll be outside.

1703
02:01:21,138 --> 02:01:24,096
Your hands are very similar to mine.

1704
02:01:27,597 --> 02:01:28,554
Sit.

1705
02:01:32,222 --> 02:01:33,096
Do you live alone?

1706
02:01:33,722 --> 02:01:34,679
No.

1707
02:01:35,305 --> 02:01:36,137
I have a wife.

1708
02:01:36,597 --> 02:01:38,762
But she is away... in Paris.

1709
02:01:39,138 --> 02:01:40,013
Sit.

1710
02:01:43,140 --> 02:01:44,056
And any...

1711
02:01:44,099 --> 02:01:45,306
children?

1712
02:01:52,057 --> 02:01:53,056
Do you ever come to India?

1713
02:01:54,140 --> 02:01:55,223
Yes.

1714
02:01:55,224 --> 02:01:58,056
I was there four years ago
when my mother passed away.

1715
02:01:59,515 --> 02:02:01,139
- Sorry.
- I have a brother there...

1716
02:02:01,140 --> 02:02:02,098
but...

1717
02:02:03,849 --> 02:02:04,973
we don't meet.

1718
02:02:10,724 --> 02:02:12,931
I've often thought about you.

1719
02:02:15,140 --> 02:02:15,931
I mean...

1720
02:02:17,515 --> 02:02:22,098
that someday, somewhere we might meet.

1721
02:02:23,683 --> 02:02:26,016
But I never figured...

1722
02:02:26,017 --> 02:02:28,683
what I would say to you.

1723
02:02:30,309 --> 02:02:31,516
Just say the truth.

1724
02:02:34,226 --> 02:02:36,475
The truth... what is the truth?

1725
02:02:37,767 --> 02:02:40,225
Everyone has their own version.

1726
02:02:45,642 --> 02:02:47,850
Look... I was...

1727
02:02:47,851 --> 02:02:49,683
25 then.

1728
02:02:50,892 --> 02:02:53,850
Rahila was a few years younger.

1729
02:02:55,101 --> 02:02:58,058
When you're young the
future doesn't matter.

1730
02:02:58,059 --> 02:02:59,558
We were just kids.

1731
02:03:02,142 --> 02:03:04,183
One day...

1732
02:03:04,309 --> 02:03:06,892
Rahila told me that she's...

1733
02:03:07,435 --> 02:03:10,268
expecting a baby.

1734
02:03:10,353 --> 02:03:13,227
I wasn't ready for the
responsibility then.

1735
02:03:13,311 --> 02:03:15,185
And nor am I now.

1736
02:03:21,811 --> 02:03:24,727
So... you just abandoned her?

1737
02:03:28,561 --> 02:03:31,560
I guess, you could say that.

1738
02:03:36,811 --> 02:03:41,227
Rahila wanted a family,
she wanted to be a mother.

1739
02:03:42,603 --> 02:03:45,143
I had other dreams.
I wanted to be an artist.

1740
02:03:46,144 --> 02:03:48,143
I wanted to paint...

1741
02:03:48,144 --> 02:03:49,728
travel the world.

1742
02:03:51,145 --> 02:03:53,644
I loved her but...

1743
02:03:53,645 --> 02:03:56,687
she made her choice and I made mine.

1744
02:03:56,771 --> 02:03:58,520
That's all.

1745
02:04:02,396 --> 02:04:04,687
I found out about you only last year.

1746
02:04:08,646 --> 02:04:09,604
But...

1747
02:04:11,230 --> 02:04:14,020
you've always known about me.

1748
02:04:15,813 --> 02:04:18,395
Did you never want to see me?

1749
02:04:20,563 --> 02:04:22,437
I thought it was better this way.

1750
02:04:30,396 --> 02:04:33,021
You asked for the truth.

1751
02:04:34,272 --> 02:04:35,438
Well, this is it.

1752
02:04:36,772 --> 02:04:37,771
Okay.

1753
02:04:38,147 --> 02:04:39,564
I... am sorry, Imran.

1754
02:04:41,523 --> 02:04:42,522
No, you're not.

1755
02:04:47,440 --> 02:04:49,939
Is there something I can do for you?

1756
02:04:51,398 --> 02:04:54,397
Apologise only when it comes from here.

1757
02:05:17,733 --> 02:05:20,690
When clouds of pain loom in the sky

1758
02:05:21,316 --> 02:05:24,274
When a shadow of sadness flickers by

1759
02:05:25,025 --> 02:05:27,983
When a tear finds it's way to the eye

1760
02:05:28,442 --> 02:05:31,399
When fear keeps the loneliness alive

1761
02:05:32,400 --> 02:05:36,941
I try and console my heart
Why is it that you cry? I ask

1762
02:05:36,942 --> 02:05:39,608
This is only what life imparts

1763
02:05:40,275 --> 02:05:42,774
These deep silences within

1764
02:05:43,150 --> 02:05:45,941
Have been handed out to all by time

1765
02:05:47,025 --> 02:05:49,608
Everyone's story has a little sorrow

1766
02:05:50,109 --> 02:05:52,941
Everyone's share has a little Sunshine

1767
02:05:54,150 --> 02:05:56,234
No need for water in your eyes

1768
02:05:57,735 --> 02:06:00,109
Every moment can be a new life

1769
02:06:01,360 --> 02:06:03,609
Why do you let them pass you by

1770
02:06:04,943 --> 02:06:07,150
Oh heart, why is it that you cry?

1771
02:06:16,194 --> 02:06:17,401
Morning...

1772
02:06:23,736 --> 02:06:24,735
Did you sleep or not?

1773
02:06:26,319 --> 02:06:26,985
No.

1774
02:06:36,194 --> 02:06:38,986
I think, we should get going.

1775
02:06:40,612 --> 02:06:41,611
Let's go.

1776
02:06:43,153 --> 02:06:43,694
Arjun...

1777
02:06:47,903 --> 02:06:49,694
I'm really sorry.

1778
02:07:14,571 --> 02:07:15,653
I'll see you at the car.

1779
02:07:15,946 --> 02:07:16,737
Yeah.

1780
02:07:20,904 --> 02:07:22,779
What do you mean,
'you slept in the car'?

1781
02:07:23,489 --> 02:07:24,863
Long story, babe.

1782
02:07:25,989 --> 02:07:26,988
Tell me, what happened?

1783
02:07:28,114 --> 02:07:30,071
Well, Imran just...

1784
02:07:31,989 --> 02:07:33,196
I'll tell you later, okay.

1785
02:07:34,030 --> 02:07:35,946
Why? Tell me now, what happened?

1786
02:07:36,114 --> 02:07:39,072
I can't tell you right now.
I'll tell you when I'm back.

1787
02:07:39,531 --> 02:07:41,114
Why are you getting irritated?

1788
02:07:41,198 --> 02:07:43,030
Why are you going on about it?

1789
02:07:43,323 --> 02:07:44,697
Okay, forget it.

1790
02:07:48,990 --> 02:07:50,155
See.

1791
02:07:50,365 --> 02:07:52,155
It's our wedding card.
Can you see it?

1792
02:07:52,406 --> 02:07:53,905
Isn't it gorgeous?

1793
02:07:54,323 --> 02:07:56,114
I'm just so happy with it.

1794
02:07:56,906 --> 02:07:59,447
Oh... I've emailed a few
options for your suit.

1795
02:07:59,448 --> 02:08:02,030
Please select one.
Okay? Don't forget.

1796
02:08:02,656 --> 02:08:03,531
Okay.

1797
02:08:05,824 --> 02:08:08,073
You are so far away.

1798
02:08:09,199 --> 02:08:10,781
You love me, right?

1799
02:08:11,991 --> 02:08:12,948
Yeah.

1800
02:08:13,824 --> 02:08:15,656
Then stop fighting with me.

1801
02:08:16,449 --> 02:08:19,615
Everything was fine before
you went on this holiday.

1802
02:08:20,199 --> 02:08:21,948
Kabir, just come home.

1803
02:08:22,574 --> 02:08:26,116
To me, your family, your friends.

1804
02:08:26,367 --> 02:08:28,116
My friends are with me.

1805
02:08:28,492 --> 02:08:30,449
Yeah, I know.
But you know what I mean.

1806
02:08:41,950 --> 02:08:49,075
Happy birthday to you...

1807
02:08:50,034 --> 02:08:53,575
Happy birthday dear Anjali...

1808
02:08:54,159 --> 02:08:56,825
Happy birthday to you...

1809
02:09:01,993 --> 02:09:03,325
What a beautifuI cake.

1810
02:09:03,368 --> 02:09:04,242
Oh my God!

1811
02:09:05,326 --> 02:09:06,533
It's beautiful!

1812
02:09:07,034 --> 02:09:08,075
- Nice, right?
- Yes!

1813
02:09:09,994 --> 02:09:11,076
Tanya?

1814
02:09:20,994 --> 02:09:22,201
What are you doing, baby?

1815
02:09:22,952 --> 02:09:24,201
I'm sorry, I'm so happy.

1816
02:09:24,785 --> 02:09:27,076
Kabir just proposed to Natasha.

1817
02:09:27,160 --> 02:09:28,201
- What
- What?

1818
02:09:28,202 --> 02:09:30,202
Oh my God!

1819
02:09:30,203 --> 02:09:33,035
You could've waited until
your mother had cut the cake.

1820
02:09:33,036 --> 02:09:36,035
Kabir, this is the best
birthday gift, ever!

1821
02:09:36,120 --> 02:09:36,994
I love you, son.

1822
02:09:36,995 --> 02:09:38,077
- The shy guy!

1823
02:09:38,953 --> 02:09:41,077
- It's a double celebration.

1824
02:09:41,078 --> 02:09:42,410
I'm so happy.

1825
02:09:43,120 --> 02:09:44,077
Now you have to call me 'mummy'.

1826
02:09:45,745 --> 02:09:47,577
- Get some champagne!

1827
02:09:50,203 --> 02:09:50,827
Come here.

1828
02:09:53,204 --> 02:09:54,703
Very good decision.

1829
02:09:56,996 --> 02:09:58,953
I'm so happy.

1830
02:10:00,037 --> 02:10:02,703
Babe, what just happened in there?

1831
02:10:02,787 --> 02:10:05,161
- What do you mean?
- I mean...

1832
02:10:05,537 --> 02:10:07,203
This ring...

1833
02:10:07,204 --> 02:10:08,703
I got it for my mom.

1834
02:10:10,704 --> 02:10:12,454
It's her birthday gift.

1835
02:10:12,997 --> 02:10:14,037
This is for your mom?

1836
02:10:14,872 --> 02:10:17,704
Look at it sweety...
it's a mummy ring.

1837
02:10:17,788 --> 02:10:19,037
What?

1838
02:10:19,038 --> 02:10:20,496
Why didn't you say something?

1839
02:10:21,080 --> 02:10:22,496
I tried.

1840
02:10:22,580 --> 02:10:26,454
But you were excited and screaming.
And Tanya made an announcement.

1841
02:10:27,038 --> 02:10:29,246
So you don't want to marry me?

1842
02:10:29,788 --> 02:10:33,204
It's not about you. I haven't
even thought about marriage.

1843
02:10:36,038 --> 02:10:37,787
What do I tell my father?

1844
02:10:42,748 --> 02:10:45,663
We'll say that we gave
it some more thought and...

1845
02:10:45,664 --> 02:10:47,997
we need more time.
That's all.

1846
02:10:47,998 --> 02:10:49,747
This is so embarrassing.

1847
02:10:50,581 --> 02:10:52,622
I'm so sorry, sweety.

1848
02:10:53,582 --> 02:10:56,206
You don't ever want to marry me?

1849
02:10:57,540 --> 02:10:59,331
It's not like that.

1850
02:10:59,332 --> 02:11:01,998
If it is, you better tell me right now!

1851
02:11:03,124 --> 02:11:05,998
I really love you, Kabir.
And I don't...

1852
02:11:05,999 --> 02:11:09,039
No, no... no sweety.
Don't cry.

1853
02:11:09,124 --> 02:11:10,039
Not now.

1854
02:11:17,540 --> 02:11:18,164
Kabir...

1855
02:11:20,124 --> 02:11:23,957
are you even serious about
this relationship or not?

1856
02:11:27,166 --> 02:11:27,957
You know what...

1857
02:11:39,001 --> 02:11:40,041
Will you marry me?

1858
02:12:04,209 --> 02:12:05,291
Who is it?

1859
02:12:20,128 --> 02:12:20,960
Room service.

1860
02:12:22,211 --> 02:12:23,002
Laila?

1861
02:12:24,044 --> 02:12:24,960
Hi!

1862
02:12:24,961 --> 02:12:25,960
Oh my God!

1863
02:12:27,253 --> 02:12:28,835
You're here... how... I mean...

1864
02:12:29,128 --> 02:12:32,002
Imran called and he begged me to come.

1865
02:12:32,169 --> 02:12:33,418
- So I came.
- Imran?

1866
02:12:34,003 --> 02:12:35,043
I knew it.

1867
02:12:35,628 --> 02:12:37,085
He is my best friend.

1868
02:12:40,253 --> 02:12:42,460
I am... so glad you're here.

1869
02:12:44,003 --> 02:12:45,585
I'm glad you are glad.

1870
02:12:48,169 --> 02:12:50,377
Hello... my the two the love the birds!

1871
02:12:50,961 --> 02:12:52,127
Hello!

1872
02:12:52,294 --> 02:12:53,378
Surprised, Arjun?

1873
02:12:54,754 --> 02:12:55,836
Thank you.

1874
02:12:55,920 --> 02:12:57,169
It's good to see you.

1875
02:12:57,170 --> 02:12:58,419
- And you.
- Hey gorgeous.

1876
02:12:58,545 --> 02:13:00,628
- I love you too.
- Nice to have you back.

1877
02:13:00,629 --> 02:13:02,087
You got a tan!

1878
02:13:02,796 --> 02:13:03,795
Get dressed, soon!

1879
02:13:03,796 --> 02:13:04,962
- We had to leave at seven.
- Correct.

1880
02:13:04,963 --> 02:13:06,212
- Two minutes?
- You missed me?

1881
02:13:06,213 --> 02:13:08,045
I always miss you, darling.

1882
02:13:08,046 --> 02:13:09,087
Where are we going?

1883
02:13:09,171 --> 02:13:10,712
It's a surprise. Can't
tell you in front of him.

1884
02:13:28,755 --> 02:13:29,962
What's going on?

1885
02:13:30,213 --> 02:13:31,295
What do you mean?

1886
02:13:31,630 --> 02:13:32,670
It's San Fermin.

1887
02:13:32,796 --> 02:13:33,837
Running with the bulls.

1888
02:13:33,838 --> 02:13:35,087
- Really?
- Didn't you know?

1889
02:13:35,171 --> 02:13:36,295
Just follow me...

1890
02:13:44,673 --> 02:13:45,756
Holy shit!

1891
02:13:52,798 --> 02:13:54,339
Are these guys mad?
What are they doing?

1892
02:13:54,632 --> 02:13:55,381
Suicide.

1893
02:13:56,048 --> 02:13:57,256
Isn't that why you are here?

1894
02:14:08,173 --> 02:14:09,964
I feIt this should be the
last experience of our trip.

1895
02:14:10,882 --> 02:14:13,214
This could be the last
experience of our life!

1896
02:14:13,632 --> 02:14:15,839
Stop it, Arjun.
Let's grab a bite.

1897
02:14:15,840 --> 02:14:16,297
Come on.

1898
02:14:17,382 --> 02:14:18,464
- Excuse me.
- Dude are you...

1899
02:14:18,465 --> 02:14:19,756
- I'm starving!

1900
02:14:21,257 --> 02:14:22,882
This is not an adventure sport.

1901
02:14:23,466 --> 02:14:24,840
I object, Judge sahab!

1902
02:14:25,383 --> 02:14:27,591
I agree it's not as
safe as regular sports.

1903
02:14:27,592 --> 02:14:29,049
And is illegal in some countries.

1904
02:14:29,050 --> 02:14:32,049
But according to the Spanish
tradition and cuIture...

1905
02:14:32,134 --> 02:14:33,049
it is allowed.

1906
02:14:33,050 --> 02:14:35,049
And technically,
according to our deal...

1907
02:14:35,134 --> 02:14:37,383
we can choose any sport, remember?

1908
02:14:37,800 --> 02:14:39,216
Imran, it's really dangerous, you know.

1909
02:14:39,217 --> 02:14:41,424
Yes, those bulls could kill us, alright?

1910
02:14:41,759 --> 02:14:44,341
We'll be dangling on their horns
like tandoori chicken on skewers!

1911
02:14:44,342 --> 02:14:46,049
Precisely the point.

1912
02:14:47,175 --> 02:14:49,258
You want to get rid of
the fear within you?

1913
02:14:49,592 --> 02:14:51,799
Well then, here's our
deepest fear. Death.

1914
02:14:52,842 --> 02:14:53,883
Let's face it.

1915
02:14:54,384 --> 02:14:55,841
Because beyond this fear...

1916
02:14:55,842 --> 02:14:56,716
lies victory!

1917
02:14:56,800 --> 02:14:58,841
Please spare us the tag lines!

1918
02:14:59,134 --> 02:15:01,008
Dude, think about it!

1919
02:15:01,050 --> 02:15:04,841
No training, no instructors.
Just us, my amigos!

1920
02:15:05,509 --> 02:15:07,259
And some bulls running after us.

1921
02:15:07,551 --> 02:15:09,926
If you want to live... just run!

1922
02:15:10,177 --> 02:15:12,385
Laila, do you know any
psychiatrist around here?

1923
02:15:13,136 --> 02:15:15,385
Because our amigo has
completely lost it!

1924
02:15:16,219 --> 02:15:18,218
I'll be at the starting line
at seven tomorrow morning.

1925
02:15:19,052 --> 02:15:21,010
With or without you.

1926
02:15:26,427 --> 02:15:27,926
I have something for you, Imran.

1927
02:15:28,761 --> 02:15:29,551
It's from Nuria.

1928
02:15:29,636 --> 02:15:30,843
Oh..

1929
02:15:33,261 --> 02:15:34,010
It's in Spanish.

1930
02:15:34,969 --> 02:15:36,301
Love has no language.

1931
02:15:37,052 --> 02:15:37,676
So true.

1932
02:15:40,719 --> 02:15:42,135
I think you should buy her something.

1933
02:15:42,927 --> 02:15:43,718
You're absolutely right.

1934
02:15:44,177 --> 02:15:45,885
Guys... shopping on
next stop?

1935
02:15:47,219 --> 02:15:48,885
Count me out, I'm going
back to the hotel.

1936
02:15:50,011 --> 02:15:51,136
Are you alright?

1937
02:15:52,012 --> 02:15:53,095
Hey.

1938
02:15:53,388 --> 02:15:54,178
I'm fine.

1939
02:15:55,013 --> 02:15:56,970
That we'll only know after a test.

1940
02:15:58,054 --> 02:15:58,803
Test?

1941
02:16:00,096 --> 02:16:01,137
What do you say, Dr. Fraud?

1942
02:16:02,013 --> 02:16:02,887
Are you game?

1943
02:16:03,388 --> 02:16:04,053
Bring it on.

1944
02:16:04,888 --> 02:16:05,970
You have to say the first thing --

1945
02:16:05,971 --> 02:16:08,178
I know the drill. Ask!

1946
02:16:09,054 --> 02:16:09,720
Black.

1947
02:16:10,013 --> 02:16:10,470
Night.

1948
02:16:10,554 --> 02:16:11,387
Sea.

1949
02:16:11,596 --> 02:16:12,262
SaIty.

1950
02:16:12,346 --> 02:16:13,137
Work.

1951
02:16:13,138 --> 02:16:14,137
Money.

1952
02:16:14,138 --> 02:16:14,970
Sex.

1953
02:16:15,221 --> 02:16:16,012
I like!

1954
02:16:16,013 --> 02:16:16,678
Friend.

1955
02:16:17,138 --> 02:16:17,803
You.

1956
02:16:18,054 --> 02:16:19,053
Marriage.

1957
02:16:20,221 --> 02:16:21,387
Family.

1958
02:16:28,221 --> 02:16:29,012
What?

1959
02:16:31,013 --> 02:16:32,387
Is that all?

1960
02:16:32,388 --> 02:16:33,763
It was enough.

1961
02:16:35,597 --> 02:16:37,180
Smartass...

1962
02:16:37,181 --> 02:16:41,055
You're using my trick on me?
Just say what you want to.

1963
02:16:41,473 --> 02:16:42,347
Okay.

1964
02:16:43,015 --> 02:16:45,514
You hesitated on 'marriage'.

1965
02:16:46,056 --> 02:16:47,305
So?

1966
02:16:47,390 --> 02:16:50,972
I'm just saying... you
hesitated... on marriage.

1967
02:16:54,973 --> 02:16:55,805
Look...

1968
02:16:56,806 --> 02:17:00,180
I don't have the time for
this crap. See you later.

1969
02:17:04,181 --> 02:17:06,722
- Okay.
- I'm sorry, I'm going to...

1970
02:17:14,598 --> 02:17:15,555
Kabir.

1971
02:17:20,724 --> 02:17:21,473
Go!

1972
02:17:24,350 --> 02:17:25,516
Kabir!

1973
02:17:26,558 --> 02:17:28,141
Kabir... man, just stop!

1974
02:17:28,767 --> 02:17:29,891
What?

1975
02:17:31,058 --> 02:17:32,891
Talk to us man. What's going on?

1976
02:17:33,142 --> 02:17:34,974
It's nothing, really.

1977
02:17:37,183 --> 02:17:38,141
Kabir...

1978
02:17:40,100 --> 02:17:42,224
Look, I'm sorry I lost my cool.

1979
02:17:43,600 --> 02:17:46,016
Because I said you have
a problem with marriage?

1980
02:17:46,850 --> 02:17:50,182
I guess, I'm freaking out. I
don't know what's happening.

1981
02:17:50,433 --> 02:17:52,849
It's normal to be nervous.

1982
02:17:52,850 --> 02:17:55,224
It's not like you're having
an arranged marriage.

1983
02:17:55,225 --> 02:17:58,057
Yeah, but she isn't
the same person I met.

1984
02:17:58,684 --> 02:18:00,850
She's changed, she's become possessive.

1985
02:18:01,393 --> 02:18:04,767
The girl I knew was a talented,
independent interior designer.

1986
02:18:04,976 --> 02:18:07,018
She enjoyed her work.

1987
02:18:07,019 --> 02:18:07,976
But now...

1988
02:18:08,435 --> 02:18:10,393
she's bid adieu to her passion and...

1989
02:18:10,685 --> 02:18:12,559
taken over my life.

1990
02:18:13,477 --> 02:18:15,476
Of course, I want a partner but...

1991
02:18:15,477 --> 02:18:17,101
I want my own life too!

1992
02:18:17,477 --> 02:18:21,226
The whole two bodies, one soul
thing I won't be able to handle it.

1993
02:18:32,102 --> 02:18:34,059
- May I ask you something?
- Yes.

1994
02:18:35,227 --> 02:18:37,518
Don't you think you
proposed to her too soon?

1995
02:18:38,185 --> 02:18:40,393
Actually, I didn't even propose.

1996
02:18:40,394 --> 02:18:42,102
- What?

1997
02:18:42,103 --> 02:18:44,269
I'd bought a ring for my
mom as a birthday gift.

1998
02:18:44,603 --> 02:18:48,102
Before giving it, I happened to show
it to Natasha and she thought...

1999
02:18:48,395 --> 02:18:49,977
it was meant for her.

2000
02:18:51,687 --> 02:18:53,311
- Are you crazy?
- What are you doing?

2001
02:18:53,896 --> 02:18:55,645
- What's wrong with him?
- What's wrong with him?

2002
02:19:01,021 --> 02:19:03,228
No wonder this vacation was
so important for you.

2003
02:19:04,146 --> 02:19:04,728
Meaning?

2004
02:19:05,896 --> 02:19:09,145
Basically, you wanted to
hear from someone else that
you shouldn't get married

2005
02:19:09,187 --> 02:19:12,061
And besides us,
who would've told you this.

2006
02:19:12,062 --> 02:19:13,895
Have you totally lost it?

2007
02:19:13,896 --> 02:19:16,478
The invites are printed. This
isn't the time to overreact!

2008
02:19:17,437 --> 02:19:18,395
Kabir.

2009
02:19:20,062 --> 02:19:21,645
We know Natasha is a great girl.

2010
02:19:21,979 --> 02:19:23,937
And we know you like her.

2011
02:19:24,355 --> 02:19:25,979
And of course, you
don't want to hurt her.

2012
02:19:27,022 --> 02:19:29,979
But ask yourseIf -- Do you
really want to marry her?

2013
02:19:30,647 --> 02:19:32,229
And if not, be honest.

2014
02:19:32,313 --> 02:19:33,937
To yourseIf and to her.

2015
02:19:34,563 --> 02:19:37,438
Of course, she'll be hurt. But in the
long run its best for both of you.

2016
02:19:37,648 --> 02:19:39,188
He is absolutely right, Kabir.

2017
02:19:39,564 --> 02:19:41,272
But I've made a commitment.

2018
02:19:41,773 --> 02:19:43,438
Okay, you screwed up.

2019
02:19:43,439 --> 02:19:45,438
No one's going to send you to prison.

2020
02:19:45,564 --> 02:19:48,022
It's not that simple.
Our parents are involved.

2021
02:19:48,273 --> 02:19:49,063
Parents?

2022
02:19:49,606 --> 02:19:50,772
Dude, it's your life.

2023
02:19:53,856 --> 02:19:55,022
You won't get it.

2024
02:19:56,231 --> 02:19:57,022
Just...

2025
02:19:57,856 --> 02:20:00,063
Just let it be, okay?
I'm sorry.

2026
02:20:00,856 --> 02:20:02,022
Kabir...

2027
02:20:05,731 --> 02:20:06,689
What a guy!

2028
02:20:25,025 --> 02:20:26,065
Laila?

2029
02:20:29,983 --> 02:20:31,024
Why're you shouting?

2030
02:20:32,108 --> 02:20:33,649
Why are you so far?

2031
02:20:48,025 --> 02:20:48,900
Better?

2032
02:20:50,067 --> 02:20:51,108
Best.

2033
02:20:54,192 --> 02:20:54,858
Ammi?

2034
02:20:56,026 --> 02:20:57,358
How are you?

2035
02:21:00,234 --> 02:21:02,191
I met Salman.

2036
02:21:08,652 --> 02:21:11,692
I now know why you and
Abu kept this from me.

2037
02:21:15,193 --> 02:21:16,276
I'm sorry, Ammi.

2038
02:21:19,235 --> 02:21:20,276
- I love you.

2039
02:21:22,027 --> 02:21:23,651
I love you too, my boy.

2040
02:23:44,075 --> 02:23:47,158
The first rocket indicates that
the pen gates have been opened.

2041
02:23:47,409 --> 02:23:49,991
Second rocket indicates that
the bulls are coming towards us.

2042
02:23:50,159 --> 02:23:52,033
We run at the second rocket.

2043
02:23:52,034 --> 02:23:52,866
Second rocket.

2044
02:23:54,409 --> 02:23:56,116
Oh San Fermin, please protect us.

2045
02:23:58,034 --> 02:23:59,199
If I die...

2046
02:23:59,659 --> 02:24:01,324
my spirit will come back to haunt you.

2047
02:24:01,867 --> 02:24:03,283
Why are you thinking about death?

2048
02:24:03,367 --> 02:24:05,324
Think about what you'll do
if you survive.

2049
02:24:10,076 --> 02:24:10,409
Listen...

2050
02:24:11,035 --> 02:24:12,159
a new pact.

2051
02:24:12,993 --> 02:24:14,617
An if-l-get out-alive pact.

2052
02:24:14,701 --> 02:24:15,742
Yeah.

2053
02:24:15,826 --> 02:24:18,284
If I get out alive,
I'll let you read my poetry.

2054
02:24:19,493 --> 02:24:21,117
Why just you?
I'll just...

2055
02:24:21,118 --> 02:24:22,118
get it published.

2056
02:24:23,202 --> 02:24:24,160
You write poetry?

2057
02:24:24,202 --> 02:24:24,993
Yes.

2058
02:24:26,994 --> 02:24:27,951
Okay.

2059
02:24:28,077 --> 02:24:30,118
If I get out alive...

2060
02:24:33,202 --> 02:24:33,826
Okay!

2061
02:24:34,161 --> 02:24:36,201
If I get out alive...

2062
02:24:36,202 --> 02:24:37,993
I'll go to Morocco with Laila.

2063
02:24:37,994 --> 02:24:39,035
Yeah!

2064
02:24:39,244 --> 02:24:40,243
That's what I'll do.

2065
02:24:40,786 --> 02:24:42,993
What's the worst that could
happen? I'll get fired.

2066
02:24:42,994 --> 02:24:43,993
- Right?
- Yeah.

2067
02:24:43,994 --> 02:24:44,993
Who cares man?

2068
02:24:44,994 --> 02:24:46,243
I'll be with her and I will live.

2069
02:24:46,702 --> 02:24:47,910
Well done, my bro!

2070
02:24:48,911 --> 02:24:49,701
Come on, Kabir.

2071
02:24:52,203 --> 02:24:52,786
Okay.

2072
02:24:52,787 --> 02:24:54,411
If I get out alive...

2073
02:24:58,578 --> 02:25:00,036
Shit guys!
The gates are open!

2074
02:25:00,453 --> 02:25:01,536
Kabir just say it.

2075
02:25:01,620 --> 02:25:03,244
It's okay, just say it.

2076
02:25:10,579 --> 02:25:13,412
If I get out alive, I'll go to London...

2077
02:25:13,413 --> 02:25:15,037
and tell Natasha that...

2078
02:25:25,079 --> 02:25:26,328
Say what? Just say it!

2079
02:25:26,663 --> 02:25:27,953
Come on, Kabir!

2080
02:25:31,913 --> 02:25:33,787
- Come on, Kabir!
- Come on!

2081
02:25:33,871 --> 02:25:36,371
I'm sorry but I can't marry you.

2082
02:25:38,622 --> 02:25:40,496
- Congratulations!
- Look out!

2083
02:28:23,212 --> 02:28:25,836
If you're carrying your
restlessness in your heart...

2084
02:28:25,837 --> 02:28:27,920
You are alive.

2085
02:28:28,004 --> 02:28:30,461
If you're carrying the lighting
of dreams in your eyes...

2086
02:28:30,546 --> 02:28:31,795
You are alive.

2087
02:28:33,212 --> 02:28:36,171
Like a gust of wind, learn to live free.

2088
02:28:36,798 --> 02:28:39,755
Learn to flow like the
waves that make a sea.

2089
02:28:40,298 --> 02:28:43,463
Let your arms be wide open,
to every moment you meet.

2090
02:28:44,089 --> 02:28:47,713
May every moment gift
you a new sight to greet.

2091
02:28:48,214 --> 02:28:50,713
If you're carrying your
wonder in your eyes...

2092
02:28:50,798 --> 02:28:52,630
You are alive.

2093
02:28:53,256 --> 02:28:56,255
If you're carrying your
restlessness in your heart...

2094
02:28:57,464 --> 02:28:58,797
You are alive.
